      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "Document models support asynchronous collaboration where contributors can work on documents without being bound by linear processes. A task document can move through different states (e.g., draft, review, approved) based on specific triggers or events. This is critical for decentralized organizations where contributors work across time zones and without synchronous coordination requirements.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:33.000Z"
